      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are picking up on a much more nuanced and potentially concerning strategy known as the \"golden handcuffs\" or containment tactic. Companies do sometimes use promotions, relocation, or specific distractions like new workspaces to isolate employees, subtly signaling their failure to challenge authority while ensuring they stay in place for safety. It is a calculated risk that rewards your value while simultaneously building walls between you and other areas of the business to prevent further disruption. However, relying on this logic for your long-term career path carries significant risk if the perspective shifts from appreciation to suppression.",
